        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Topic modeling is frequently employed",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "for discovering structures ( or patterns ) in a corpus of documents . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Its utility in text - mining and document retrieval tasks in various fields of scientific research is rather well known . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "An unsupervised machine learning approach , Latent Dirichlet Allocation ( LDA ) has particularly been utilized",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "for identifying latent ( or hidden ) topics in document collections",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "and for deciphering the words",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "that define one or more topics",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "using a generative statistical model . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Here we describe",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "how SARS - CoV-2 genomic mutation profiles can be structured into a ' Bag of Words '",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "to enable identification of signatures ( topics ) and their probabilistic distribution across various genomes",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "using LDA . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Topic models were generated",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "using ~47000 novel corona virus genomes",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "( considered as documents ) ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "leading to identification of 16 amino acid mutation signatures and 18 nucleotide mutation signatures",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "( equivalent to topics )",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "in the corpus of chosen genomes through coherence optimization . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "The document assumption for genomes also helped in identification of contextual nucleotide mutation signatures in the form of conventional Ngrams",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "( e.g. bi - grams and tri - grams ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "We validated the signatures",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "obtained",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 22,
            "text": "using LDA driven method",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 24,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "against the previously reported recurrent mutations and phylogenetic clades for genomes . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 25,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "Additionally , we report the geographical distribution of the identified mutation signatures in SARS - CoV-2 genomes on the global map . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 26,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "Use of the non - phylogenetic albeit classical approaches like topic modeling and other data centric pattern mining algorithms is therefore proposed for supplementing the efforts",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 27,
            "parent": 26,
            "text": "towards understanding the genomic diversity of the evolving SARS - CoV-2 genomes ( and other pathogens / microbes ) . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        }
    ]
}